INTRODUCTION AND READING OF BILLS

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to introduce and pass legislation that would reduce the threshold amount of child support arrears due and owing before drivers, professional, occupational, business, and recreational licenses of a child support obligee can be suspended from the equivalent of four months of arrears to the equivalent of two months of arrears.
EventItemMatterName: Reduce the threshold amount of child support arrears due and owing before drivers, professional, occupational, business, and recreational licenses of a child support obligee can be suspended from the equivalent of four months of arrear.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to mandating the issuance of fire service elevator express keys to emergency medical service personnel when they begin their tour of duty.
EventItemMatterName: Mandating the issuance of fire service elevator express keys to emergency medical service personnel when they begin their tour of duty.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the Governor and the Legislature of the State of New York to enact legislation that would reduce certain factors contributing to wrongful convictions and to establish an independent commission that would conduct a comprehensive study of wrongful convictions in the State.
EventItemMatterName: Reduce certain factors contributing to wrongful convictions and to establish an independent commission that would conduct a comprehensive study of wrongful convictions in the State.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution expressing the Council’s support for the “Uterine Fibroid Research and Education Act of 2007” (H.R. 2349 and S. 1275), which would provide funding for research and education with respect to uterine fibroids.
EventItemMatterName: Support for the “Uterine Fibroid Research and Education Act of 2007” (H.R. 2349 and S. 1275)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Veterans
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to pass legislation that would guarantee full payment of enlistment bonuses and incentives to veterans wounded in combat.
EventItemMatterName: Congress to pass legislation that would guarantee full payment of enlistment bonuses and incentives to veterans wounded in combat.
